#: chaotic_pfc.config.SpectralConfig:9 of
msgid ""
"FIR window applied to each Welch segment. Currently ``\"hamming\"`` (the "
"historical default) and ``\"kaiser\"`` are supported."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SpectralConfig:13 of
msgid "str"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SpectralConfig:17 of
msgid ""
"Shape parameter of the Kaiser window. Ignored unless ``window == "
"\"kaiser\"``. Larger values give higher stop-band attenuation at the cost"
" of a wider main lobe; β ≈ 5 is a common ~50 dB compromise."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.LyapunovConfig:5 of
msgid ""
"Iterations used for the estimate and the transient to discard before "
"starting to accumulate."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.LyapunovConfig:10 of
msgid ""
"Half-width of the IC sampling box around the fixed point, as a fraction "
"of the coordinate (±10% by default)."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.LyapunovConfig:17 of
msgid "Filter gain term used in the 4-D pole-filtered system."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.LyapunovConfig:23 of
msgid ""
"Pole radius ``r ∈ (0, 1)``. Larger values make the filter sharper and the"
" dynamics more dissipative."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.LyapunovConfig:30 of
msgid "Normalised angular frequency of the pole pair (``× π``)."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SweepConfig:3 of
msgid ""
"Used by :mod:`chaotic_pfc.sweep`. The full grid is ``len(orders) × "
"n_cutoffs`` points; at the defaults this is 4 000."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SweepConfig:8 of
msgid "Burn-in iterations applied before computing the estimator."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SweepConfig:14 of
msgid "Iterations accumulated into the Lyapunov estimator."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SweepConfig:20 of
msgid "Number of random initial conditions averaged per grid point."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.config.SweepConfig:26 of
